'It was at the end of the 60s or the beginning of the 70s,' he said, adding that his wife found out about it.

He said she realised how 'close' it was and offered to leave him. 

'I told her that was a totally fallacious idea,' he added.

According to Stern, the woman was a colleague in the social democrat party which he led.

He remained in contact with her 'for a long while' after the break up and attended her funeral two years ago.  

